Kitchen Scissors Vegetable peeler Kitchen Knife Sharpener

7" Santoku Knife It is perfect for mincing, dicing and slicing. The hollow end of the Santoku knife produces less friction which gives faster and more precise cutting results. It’s great for thin delicate slices. 8" Bread Knife The serrated edge of the bread knife makes it perfect for cutting any food that is hard on the outside and soft on the outside. It cuts through the harder, outer edge without crushing or squishing the food. 8" Chef Knife This is the most versatile and most often used knife in the kitchen knife set. It has a slightly curved blade that is perfect for most cooking tasks that include chopping and mincing.

5" Utility Knife This knife is between the paring knife and the Chef’s knife in length and is great for mincing vegetables and fruits. 3.5" Paring Knife The straight edge of a paring knife helps peel the skins from fruits and vegetables very easily. It’s most often used for peeling, shaping and decorative cuts. 8" Carving Knife Carving knife is made in more flexible and more rigid designs. The blade is thinner than that of the Chef’s knife and is great for carving needs such as turkey, ham and roasts.

I think it's great that all of the knives are housed in a stand so you can see them all clearly. I appreciate that they also include a set of scissors, a plier, and a knife sharpener. reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Really Nice Set Easy to Keep on Counter
reviews.reviewText: Knife Set BETTER THAN EXPECTED! I am Disabled and need easy access to everything including silverware and cooking knives. I hate going through drawers to find either. So I have a hanging silverware Set(4 place) on a small rack on my kitchen counter and needed a knife set. This set is Not Only Beautiful but the acrylic holder displays them compactly narrow, handy, and Beautifully on the counter as well. The knives are well made.I got these BLUE ONES because I have friends that come over and cook and barbecue with me and sometimes (when they clean up) and take some left over food for their kids home the large bowls sometimes have my small knives in them. They bring them back but I figure the BLUE ONES will stand out so they can find them easier than the normal Stainless Steel ones and I'll get them back sooner. They don't take the knives on purpose but you know how it is when you are trying to cleanup fast with a bunch of children around and your concentration is broken that some utensils in the bowls can get packed up by mistake to. The mother is all apologies when she realizes what has happened when she gets home and I laugh because I know her & her family and know it is just an oversight on her part as a mother. It's fun to see but frustrating when I need one of the knives and I don't have it. So... NOW! THESE BLUE ONES WILL REALLY STAND OUT and solve (the Problem?) LOL And... THEY ARE WELL MADE, COMFORTABLE TO HOLD, AND BEAUTIFUL to see. I think you will REALLY LIKE THEM.

Reviewed in the United States on July 20, 2020
reviews.reviewText: I like these knives quite a bit. I've done my kitchen in blue, and these fit right in. They look good on the counter, not some generic ugly wooden block. Also, because of the openness of the stand design, I can let the knives air dry right in their stand without worrying about wood getting moldy or nasty. You can easily clean inside the stand.The knives themselves are very sharp. No issues with the color coating. I like that there's a sharpener, vegetable peeler, and scissors with it. Haven't had a chance to use the sharpener or the vegetable peeler yet. They're fairly comfortable to hold, and I like them very much. The only reason I gave it 4 stars instead of 5 is because they're definitely not full tang, and have this textured plastic handle, so I'm worried how long they will last. I may come back and raise or lower the rating depending on their longevity. I'm happy with my purchase though.***Update***So I’ve had these knives a while and I’m definitely not as impressed. I mentioned them not being full tang and sure enough one has come apart. The others are still together and work fine. They have also discolored though. All of them. And very shortly after receiving them. They just very quickly get off-colored spots and brown spots.Also, the tip on the chefs knife bent the very first time I used it. I did not stab into anything. I didn’t like stab it into the cutting board or anything. Just one minute it’s straight, next it’s bent. I literally have no idea how it could have happened. I have since used pliers to straighten it out and it’s working fine again.I still love the stand. The scissors and the vegetable peeler are fantastic. Knife sharpener is super handy. If you really like the look of the knives, they’re not a terrible purchase for the price point. But I wouldn’t buy these again.

reviews.reviewTitle: Optik ist nicht alles lassen total nach
reviews.reviewText: Ich besitze diesen Block nun schon eine ganze Weile und habe ihn gut getestet.Nach Erhalt war ich von der Optik und Schärfe total begeistert. Die Messer liegen gut in der Hand und waren für mich als rollstuhlfahrende Köchin eine Hilfe.Am Anfang !!!Obwohl ich diese Messer gehegt und gepflegt habe, sie nicht in unseren Geschirrspüler tat entstanden zuerst leichte Rostflecke wenn man sie nicht gleich abtrocknen. Man bekam sie aber weg.Mittlerweile sind die Messer unansehlich und von Schärfe keine Spur mehr.Ok man könnte nun sagen da ist ein Messerschärfer dabei aber leider nutzt meiner überhaupt nix.Ich finde das sehr schade als Kunde schmeißt man hier das Geld zum Fenster raus.Vielleicht habe ich auch nur einen "Montagsblock" erwischt.Leider kann ich keine Kaufempfehlung aussprechen.Dies ist eine ehrlich verfasste Rezension nach einigen Wochen Test und nicht gleich voller Euphorie nach Erhalt der Ware.Ich hoffe sie war hilfreich.
